# Changelog Format Rules

## Raycast Extensions Monorepo Compliance
- Top entry for new PRs must use `[PR_MERGE_DATE]` placeholder (not `2026-04-28`)
- Format: `## [Short Title] [Version] - [PR_MERGE_DATE]`
- For historical entries with actual dates: `## [Short Title] [Version] - YYYY-MM-DD`

## Consistency
- All entries use consistent header pattern: `## [Title] [Version] - Date`
- Keep bullets **end-user facing** (this is what Raycast surfaces in Version History)
- Avoid internal refactor diaries; focus on user-visible changes
- Normalise spelling and capitalisation (e.g. "README", "Favourites" not "Favorites")

## Content Guidelines
- Each bullet should describe a user-visible change
- Group related changes under subheadings when appropriate
- Use UK English spelling throughout
- Be concise and specific
